{
  "name": "devsecops-agency",
  "version": "0.4.0",
  "description": "A fully autonomous AI software-development company in a plugin. You speak only to the CEO; the CEO runs a board of 16 Chiefs; each Chief runs a council of specialists; specialists may, when work shards cleanly, spawn workers to run in parallel. Research-first, security-second, receipts-always. STRIDE + OWASP Top 10 baseline for code; OWASP ASI Top 10 2025 via the Red-Team Council; every shipped artifact gets SBOM + SLSA provenance; DLP on every outbound tool call; secrets only via vault refs; runtime-hook enforcement of commit-gate, secrets-scanner, tool-guardian, governance-audit, dependency-license-checker, session-logger. 1 CEO + 16 Chiefs + 75 specialists = 92 agents; Audit / Evaluation / Red-Team / SRE are informing + independent — never on any project's delivery path. v0.4.0 'Governance+Resilience' — the final of four staggered waves (v0.3.7 Clarity → v0.3.8 Identity+Learning → v0.3.9 Rhythm+Career → v0.4.0 Governance+Resilience). Adds GOVERNANCE.md + RESILIENCE.md at repo root and two new skills. GOVERNANCE.md is the decision matrix: Proposer / Reviewer / Approver / Final-vote per decision kind across ~22 rows; enumerates the 10 USER-ONLY actions (kickoff, tier change, fire, waive blocking red, Rung 7 park, amend root docs, publish externally, spend money, accept non-goal, cross-tier repurpose); distinguishes blocking chiefs (CISO, CEVO, CRT, CAO — strict veto, clearable only by user waiver) from informing-only chiefs (CSRE + CPO/CTO/VP-Eng/CQO/VP-Ops/CKO/GC/CMO/CSO/COO — raise ADRs, not vetoes). RESILIENCE.md is the failure-mode map: 15+ rows mapping each failure (model-outage, tool-outage, fix-loop cap, blocking red, Keeper-Test red, missed heartbeat, append-only violation, raw secret, prompt-diff reject, red-team critical, eval regression, budget burn, chief-unavailable, worker stuck, user unavailable) to first response + escalation path + skill(s) + ADR kind; defines four degraded modes (model, heartbeat, chief, budget — any subset active simultaneously) and five recovery guarantees (no silent failure, no lost work, no double-decision, recovery window, paper trail survives agent). Two new skills: waivers/ (formal time-boxed waiver flow for blocking-council reds; proposer = council lead, reviewer = blocking chief + CEO, approver = user-only; every waiver has a calendar expiration ≤ 90 days; paired waiver-expiry ADR files on expiry day via rhythm heartbeat; one-finding-one-artifact-one-project scope; ASI-class + raw-secret findings not waivable), drill/ (scheduled + on-demand resilience drills across 5 drill kinds on 4 cadences: monthly chief-unavailable, quarterly heartbeat-miss + model-outage, annual waiver-expiry + compaction-loss, on-demand; every drill files a drill-report ADR with outcome pass / pass-with-gaps / fail; missed drills are CAO reds; drills never run during a live incident affecting the same subsystem). CEO SKILL.md now reads GOVERNANCE+RESILIENCE at session start alongside MISSION+VALUES+LESSONS; AGENTS.md + skills/AGENTS.md updated with 13 new anti-patterns + 2 new skill-index rows. Skill-layer and root-doc-layer only — no new agents, no new councils, no new tool grants. Full wave-by-wave history (v0.2.0 → v0.3.9) is in CHANGELOG.md.",
